<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="tbarticle" summary="article">
<tr class="txttop">

<td>I found this infor on another guilds web page, they found it at eqlive, is some interesting developments about horses:<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
"It's kind of funny...but when I made that statement, I wasn't even talking about the warhorse.<br />
<br />
To be clear on that, though, Knights that have the /claim item will be able to get their special mounts upgraded to a warhorse as will anyone who turns in any other horse bridle including the ornate ones.<br />
<br />
What I was referring to was a long standing request from Shadowknights in particular. For as long as Nightmares have been in game, SKs have been asking to be able to ride them. Unfortunately, that model wasn't built as a mount so it wasn't doable. With PoR, we made a new nightmare model so when we created it, we built it to be usable as a mount. Barring any unforeseen problems between now and launch, SKs will have a new AA they can purchase to get a nightmare mount. <br />
<br />
We also built a new version of the Nightmare's antithesis, the Unicorn, and Paladin will get that as an AA mount. These are not PoR AAs, but rather general AAs available to anyone.<br />
<br />
Rashere"<br />
<br />
and further down the post chain<br />
<br />
"They're seperate AAs so you can choose to use either the normal horse or the Nightmare/Unicorn.<br />
<br />
Rashere"<br />
<br />
<br />
more info:<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
So, there's 3 different things going on with mounts. Let me run through them real quick:<br />
<br />
1) The /claim mount. The /claim item itself will summon a slow tan horse. You can combine that /claim item with any horse bridle (including emp/seru horses) to get a warhorse version of that bridle. Combining a black silk bridle with the /claim item will give you a fast black horse, for instance. You can split them back into the /claim item and the bridle if you ever want to apply the /claim item to a different horse.<br />
<br />
2) The SK/Paly AA mounts. You can talk to a certain vendor in the bazaar, show them your /claim item, and they will give you an addition rank of those AA mounts that summons the warhorse version of those mounts instead of the normal one. This is an AA ability change, so a permanent upgrade. Be sure you like the warhorse before upgrading.<br />
<br />
3) The SK/Paly special mounts (nightmare and unicorn). These are a brand new AA ability and you can choose to use either these or the normal AA mounts at any point once you've bought them.<br />
<br />
Rashere<br />
<br />
About other types of mounts<br />
<br />
Nope, the barding (the /claim item) can only be applied to horses, not drogmor or roboboars.<br />
<br />
Rashere<br />
<br />
The /claim item summons its own warhorse. It's a slow, tan WARhorse. <br />
<br />
Sorry for the confusion.<br />
<br />
Rashere<br />
<br />
"Does it eat gnomes"<br />
Only if you hold the gnome in the palm of your hand and offer it to it like a carrot.<br />
<br />
Rashere</td>
</tr>
